def: Bearing sarments, or runners, as the strawberry.

a. & n. from Strike, v. Striking distance, the distance throughwhich an object can be reached by striking; the distance at which aforce is effective when directed to a particular object.-- Striking plate. (a) The plate against which the latch of a doorlock strikes as the door is closed. (b) A part of the centering of anarch, which is driven back to loosen the centering in striking it.
To strike out; to strike faster than. Shak.
A substance resembling gutta-percha, and used to adulterate it,obtained from the East Indian tree Isonandra acuminata.
A compound of a binary type containing two cyanogen groups orradicals; -- called also bicyanide.
Having the nerves spring from the midrib.
The quality or state of being sleepy.
To appoint previously, or beforehand. Carlyle.
